  "phq9_impact": "If you checked off any problems, how difficult have these problems made it for you to do your work, take care of things at home, or get along with other people? ",
  "phq9_impact_chk0": "Not difficult at all",
  "phq9_impact_chk1": "Somewhat difficult",
  "phq9_impact_chk2": "Very difficult",
  "phq9_impact_chk3": "Extremely difficult",
  "phq9_suggestion_1": "Major depressive disorder (MDD) is suggested if:",
  "phq9_suggestion_1_why_1": "Of the 9 items,5 or more are checked as at least more than half the days",
  "phq9_suggestion_1_why_2": "Either item 1 or 2 is checked as at least 'more than half the days'",
  "phq9_suggestion_2": "Other depressive syndrome is suggested if:",
  "phq9_suggestion_2_why_1": "Of the 9 items, between 2 to 4 are checked as at least more than half the days:",
  "phq9_suggestion_2_why_2": "Either item 1 or 2 is checked as at least 'more than half the days'",
  "phq9_scoring_instructions": "PHQ-9 scores can be used to plan and monitor treatment. To score the instrument, tally the numbers of all the checked responses under each heading (not at all=0, several days=1, more than half the days=2, and nearly every day=3). Add the numbers together to total the score on the bottom of the questionnaire. Interpret the score by using the guide listed below.  ",
